MountainRange(x) ::: x is a mountain range.

Visit(juan, picuris) ::: Juan de Onate visited the Picuris Mountains.
Mine(harding) ∧ LocatedIn(harding, picuris) ∧ Donated(harding) ::: The Harding Pegmatite Mine, located in the Picuris Mountains, was donated.
¬∃x ∃y (MountainRange(y) ∧ In(y, texas) ∧ Mine(x) ∧ LocatedIn(x, y) ∧ Donated(x)) ::: There are no mountain ranges in texas that have mines which have been donated.
Conclusion:
¬(LocatedIn(harding, newMexico) ∧ MountainRange(newMexico)) ::: The Harding Pegmatite Mine is not located in a mountain range in New Mexico.
